This topic explains how to install Ops Manager on GCP using Terraform.

## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

You can install Ops Manager on GCP with either the Pivotal Application Service (PAS) or VMware Tanzu Kubernetes Grid Integrated Edition (TKGI) runtime.

To install Ops Manager on GCP using Terraform, do one of the following:

* Install with PAS. See [Install on PAS Using Terraform](#terraform-pas).
* Install with TKGI. See [Install on TKGI Using Terraform](#terraform-pks).

## <a id="terraform-pas"></a> Install with PAS Using Terraform

To install with PAS using Terraform, do the following:

1. Deploy Ops Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on GCP Using Terraform](../gcp/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on GCP Using Terraform](../gcp/config-terraform.html).

1. (Optional) Configure a shared VPC. See [(Optional) Configuring a Shared VPC on GCP](./gcp-shared-vpc.html).

## <a id="terraform-pks"></a> Install with TKGI Using Terraform

To install with TKGI using Terraform, do the following:

1. Deploy Ops Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on GCP Using Terraform](../gcp/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on GCP Using Terraform](../gcp/config-terraform.html).

1. (Optional). Configure a shared VPC. See [(Optional) Configuring a Shared VPC on GCP](./gcp-shared-vpc.html).

